</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BB6355278788DD6A902BB14F00D27A41" pageId="186" pageNumber="187" type="description">
<paragraph id="90E7ABEE1A99BFE3FB3F68EC45A56762" pageId="186" pageNumber="187">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="56ACE8FD22867305D553737C9ADA312A" pageId="186" pageNumber="187">
Villous perennial to 40 cm. Leaves sessile, 1.3-7 
<normalizedToken id="02AEFC347BBEAC05DC14C76998FA42D6" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.4-1.2 cm, oblong to oblanceolate, acute, margin entire, attenuate at the base, softly white-villous. Flowers in dense axillary heads; peduncles 1.5-3.5 cm, exceeding bracts; bracteoles 6-15 
<normalizedToken id="4BACF624D85A6B6D6FEAF8A75E42035F" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-2 mm, linear-lanceolate, acuminate, densely villous; outer sepals 7-10 
<normalizedToken id="073AC98C76CFB0B0F920745BFE6702AE" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3 mm, lanceolate, acuminate, inner sepals narrower, 1-2 mm wide; corolla 2-2.5 cm, unlobed, midpetaline bands pubescent, terminating in a tooth; ovary and style glabrous; style divided c. 3 mm above base, the stigmas 5 mm, longer than the united part of the style. [
<bibRefCitation id="03C0FFC6CF259CE04D01DC2BD1EC49E2" author="Sa'ad, F" journalOrPublisher="Bronder Offset, Rotterdam" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 287" refId="B314" refString="Sa'ad, F, 1967. The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht. Bronder Offset, Rotterdam: 1 - 287" title="The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht" year="1967">
<normalizedToken id="31CAEF27B88268FB3F3FE5312C8C3C08" originalValue="Sa’ad">Sa'ad</normalizedToken>
1967
</bibRefCitation>
: 169; 
<bibRefCitation id="C89E07501880A332449053CC436146A1" author="Boulos, L" journalOrPublisher="Flora of Egypt" pageId="200" pageNumber="201" pagination="242 - 267" refId="B59" refString="Boulos, L, 2000. . Flora of Egypt 2: 242 - 267" volume="2" year="2000">Boulos 2000</bibRefCitation>
: 247]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4A8D8C096250751AC68329B8C4BB7CE9" pageId="186" pageNumber="187" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="FF8C870344E659B755E8A3F074D582C8" pageId="186" pageNumber="187">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="03500F2C361F944A480349B2C39E91DE" pageId="186" pageNumber="187">
Egypt: Sinai (
<emphasis id="99EB203EA38567C3B51B2EEC1446DA92" italics="true" pageId="186" pageNumber="187">
<normalizedToken id="0CAF35AFE97B2B300FDDEAD89CEEA25B" originalValue="Bové">Bove</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
503, 
<emphasis id="B928C27A6CC6A4CAB68AF2355B464A5F" italics="true" pageId="186" pageNumber="187">Danin</emphasis>
s.n. [28/5/1962]), Jordan: Wadi Sirhan (
<emphasis id="5DBF75789414769C9853EA3223E72513" italics="true" pageId="186" pageNumber="187">Hunting Survey</emphasis>
117a). Apparently very rare.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="25D7FF906828945D5CE0F2977B1F1641" pageId="186" pageNumber="187" type="notes">
<paragraph id="A68AAAAF61EA55B271A3642F57F50D6E" pageId="186" pageNumber="187">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="365986966E036AC2BBCC068A3BC44C9E" pageId="186" pageNumber="187">
Differs from the two previous species in the pedunculate heads but superficially identical to 
<taxonomicName id="72C67FD960D820F63442354FEEFF8E4D" authorityName="J. R. I. Wood &amp; R. W. Scotland" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Wood &amp; Williams &amp; Mitchell &amp; Carine &amp; Harris &amp; Scotland" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus cephalopodus subsp. bushiricus" order="Solanales" pageId="186" pageNumber="187" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="cephalopodus" subSpecies="bushiricus">Convolvulus cephalopodus subsp. bushiricus</taxonomicName>
, from which it is distinguished by the glabrous ovary. Very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="FA589AB69AFC421620F4BBBE934258E5" authorityName="Boiss., Diagn. Pl. Orient. 11: 81. 1849. (Boissier" authorityYear="1849" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus schimperi" order="Solanales" pageId="186" pageNumber="187" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="schimperi">
<emphasis id="B9B8E4BA6E748B4E6224CB807F231B78" italics="true" pageId="186" pageNumber="187">Convolvulus schimperi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differing in the ascending habit and in the leaves which are not undulate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1EE180A9C14DE98C8373A205B3340EF8" pageId="186" pageNumber="187">The lectotype is a meagre specimen and all the other cited specimens represent more complete material.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
